LogFile.FinalText: In many homes you will find a pet, and most people prefer either a dog or a cat. So far, the plushy little dog beats the cute kitten in the race to be the most popular pet in Denmark. The loyalty of the dog explains its big popularity, whereas the big number of cat owners love the individuality of the cat. The common cat owner finds a dog too less individual and too dirty, but many dog owners see cats as lazy and unpersonal animals. Many pet owners choose a pet that reflects their own personality. When the big strong man buys a big strong dog, the dog threngthens the man's ego. On the contrary, the feminine woman often prefers the beautiful and elegant cat. The dog and the cat can normally get along without problems, if they are used to each other. The owners of the dogs and cats often have more trouble between them than the dog and the cat themselves.
